    <!-- 🏖️ Jetty Park Beach -->
    <section class="card">
      <h2>Jetty Park Beach · Cape Canaveral · Best for Little Ones</h2>
      <p class="muted">400 E Jetty Rd · ~50 min from MCO · ~60 min from Universal/Royal Pacific</p>

      <h3>Why It’s #1 for Non‑Swimmers</h3>
      <ul class="simple-list small">
        <li>Protected cove on south side — calm, shallow, virtually wave‑free.</li>
        <li>No rip currents · Gradual sandy slope · Kids can wade freely.</li>
        <li>Tidal pools with crabs, barnacles, mussels, tiny fish — endlessly fascinating.</li>
        <li>Bonus: Direct line‑of‑sight to Kennedy Space Center launch pads 1.5 mi north.</li>
        <li>Water avg 82–84°F · Virtually no waves on protected jetty side.</li>
        <li>Lifeguards on duty in summer · Parking $15/day · Restrooms, showers, playground, picnic tables.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Pros & Cons</h3>
      <ul class="simple-list small">
        <li>✅ Calm protected water · Tidal pools kids love · Playground on‑site · Less crowded than Cocoa Beach · Lifeguards on duty</li>
        <li>❌ Smaller footprint · No surf shops · Basic snack options · 5 min farther from MCO than Cocoa Beach</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="small"><strong>Best for:</strong> Families with toddlers and young non‑swimmers who want calm water, tidal pools, and possible rocket launch views.</p>

      <h3>Beach Bag Essentials</h3>
      <p class="small">Sunscreen SPF 50+, towels, change of clothes, swim gear, snacks, water bottles, small bucket + shovel, boogie board (optional), water shoes (essential for tidal pools), swim diapers if needed.</p>

      <h3>Launch Tips</h3>
      <p class="small">SpaceX Starlink launches occur every 1–2 weeks · Check spaceflightnow.com and Space Launch Now app around Jul 1–5 for launches during trip window — often visible from parks!</p>
      <p class="small">💡 If a launch is scheduled during your parks week, night launches are visible from Magic Kingdom or EPCOT parking areas — set an alert in Space Launch Now app.</p>
    </section>

